                            <comment id="14542922" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 13 May 2015 23:42:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Good timing, we are evaluating G1 for production now and can confirm or add details, either here or on a follow up. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15176615" author="ndimiduk" created="Wed, 2 Mar 2016 22:35:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How&apos;d the evaluation go &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=apurtell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;apurtell&quot;&gt;Andrew Purtell&lt;/a&gt;? Anyone else have some pearls of wisdom to distill here? Maybe &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=vrodionov&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;vrodionov&quot;&gt;Vladimir Rodionov&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15176657" author="bbeaudreault" created="Wed, 2 Mar 2016 22:57:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We will be publishing a blog post very soon, which has some lessons learned from some very thorough G1 testing/tuning we&apos;ve recently done (based on our use case at least). I&apos;ll update this ticket when we have that available, which you guys can feel free to use as you will&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15176732" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 2 Mar 2016 23:46:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It went well. We are making the switch. Let me ask the guys on our perf team if they&apos;re interested in blogging about it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15280476" author="davelatham" created="Wed, 11 May 2016 17:23:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hubspot&apos;s post: &lt;a href=&quot;http://product.hubspot.com/blog/g1gc-tuning-your-hbase-cluster&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://product.hubspot.com/blog/g1gc-tuning-your-hbase-cluster&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
